@startuml
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
title Nightfall - Deployment & Project Structure (Pure Browser + Godot 4 Web)

cloud "Static Hosting (GitHub Pages / Cloudflare / S3)" as Host {
  folder "Godot Web Export" {
    artifact "index.html"
    artifact "nightfall.js"
    artifact "nightfall.wasm"
    artifact "nightfall.pck"
    artifact "godot.editor.html"
  }

  folder "WebLLM Nano Models" {
    artifact "phi-2-q4f16_1-webgpu.wasm"
    artifact "mlc-chat-config.json"
    artifact "ndarray-cache.json"
    artifact "params_shard_*.bin"
  }

  folder "Assets (Imported into .pck)" {
    artifact "player/"
    artifact "cats/"
    artifact "environment/"
    artifact "ui/"
    artifact "sounds/"
  }
}

node "Client Browser" as Browser {
  component "Godot 4 Web Engine" as GodotEngine
  component "WebLLM Runtime" as WebLLM
  component "WebGPU" as GPU
  database "IndexedDB" as Cache
}

actor "Human Player" as Player

' Flow
Player --> GodotEngine : "WASD + Mouse + Interaction"
GodotEngine --> WebLLM : "Query nano model for cat behavior"
WebLLM --> GPU : "Inference on nano models"
GodotEngine <--> Cache : "Load model weights & game assets"

note right of GodotEngine
  Recommended Godot Project Tree:

  nightfall/
  ├── project.godot
  ├── main.tscn                  ← Entry point scene
  ├── autoload/
  │   ├── GameManager.gd         ← Central orchestration + event bus
  │   ├── StateManager.gd        ← Persistent game state
  │   └── WebLLMConnector.gd     ← Bridge to WebLLM nano models
  ├── player/
  │   ├── Player.tscn            ← CharacterBody3D + Camera3D
  │   ├── Player.gd              ← Input, movement, heart rate, inventory
  │   └── components/
  │       ├── HeartRate.gd
  │       ├── Inventory.gd
  │       └── Flashlight.gd
  ├── cats/
  │   ├── Cat.tscn               ← CharacterBody3D template
  │   ├── Cat.gd                 ← Vision, state machine
  │   └── ai/
  │       ├── CatBrain.gd        ← Nano-model prompting & decision making
  │       └── behaviors/
  │           ├── Wander.gd
  │           ├── Mischief.gd
  │           └── Flee.gd
  ├── environment/
  │   ├── House.tscn
  │   ├── Curtains.gd
  │   ├── Lights/
  │   │   ├── StaticWindowLight.tscn   ← OmniLight3D outside windows
  │   │   └── FlickeringLight.gd
  │   └── props/
  ├── interactables/
  │   ├── Note.tscn
  │   ├── Door.tscn
  │   ├── Button.tscn
  │   └── Interactable.gd        ← Base script with _on_interacted()
  ├── ui/
  │   ├── HUD.tscn
  │   ├── HeartMonitor.tscn
  │   └── CurtainReveal.tscn
  ├── assets/
  │   ├── models/
  │   ├── textures/
  │   └── sounds/
  └── web_harness/
      ├── WebLLM.gd              ← JavaScript bridge via JavaScriptBridge
      └── EventBus.gd            ← Godot Signal based reactivity
end note

note bottom of GodotEngine
  • Godot 4 natively supports event-driven architecture via Signals.
  • No extra framework needed — use connect() / emit_signal().
  • GameManager acts as central orchestrator.
  • Player actions (open curtain, make noise) emit signals that cats react to.
  • Reactivity achieved through Godot’s built-in _process(), Signals,
    and reactive GDScript properties (using @export and setters).
  • WebLLMConnector uses Godot’s JavaScriptBridge to call browser nano models.
end note

note right of WebLLM
  Nano models (Phi-2, TinyLlama, Gemma-2B quantized)
  run completely in-browser via WebLLM.
  Each cat maintains a tiny rolling context.
end note

@enduml
